    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>Determine the value of <m>b</m> to make <m>f(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=-1</m>. Explain your reasoning using limits.</p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        f(x) = \begin{cases}
                        b x + 5 \, x^{2} - 6, &amp; x \leq -1 \\
                        \frac{1}{2} \, x + \frac{7}{2}, &amp; x &gt; -1
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
Classify the type of discontinuity present at <m>x=-6</m> for 
the function <m>g(x)</m>. Explain your reasoning using limits. </p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        g(x) = \begin{cases}
                        -4 \, x - 17, &amp; x &lt; -6 \\
                        9, &amp; x = -6 \\
                        -3 \, x - 9, &amp; x &gt; -6 \\
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>To make <m>f(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=-1</m>, let <m>b=-4</m>.</li>
                <li>
The function <m>g(x)</m> has a
jump discontinuity.
                </li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
